
    The Johannesburg Roads Agency (JRA) has announced that certain roads in Joburg will be closed for New Year’s Eve festivities.All roads leading to the M1 North and South on the Double Decker (DD) section for New Year’s Eve celebrations will be closed, according to the Agency.The roads will be closed at 20:00 on December 31 and will be reopened after 01:00 on New Year’s Day.The following sections will be completely closed:1. M1 South Smit Street on-ramp – motorists are advised to use Smit Street off-ramp.2. M1 South Carr Street on-ramp3. M1 North: Crown interchange to DD - motorists are advised to use M2 East4. M2 West: Crown interchange to DD5. M1 North on-ramp from Booysens Road: Selby to M1 North DDif(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjssmj5nwR1UjxEZTSwi23IImc6w0nAPqfwBZPVOE7xYg4bPP3_38sVG-kg_bV4qSnYGEWWug6wnlMJkA6ZF6nntZbQuMEldLR_KKlGBxf-HbggPymDpK2lxJIrJhK-1VhidEVW6yJNOW5_iPRK9z4NsRnKABOcuOSp3N-mr1On-9ABbJ-BvpdBQNvrfcRKS84vZCVn8K7kR5YVpbuRBzvtTn4ZMVEr0dt5LIN0tGQqBfFMbY-VthqIvmZFiBx-KcSFB5oZIQ1b44feWC2LaXlYLmMrTrF6s\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzGyNU8oCX7tWEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
